Summary:
### Lucius Fox

- Your interactions with Alfred clearly indicated that you two were not a team, and him being evil cleared you a long time ago. Besides that, you've gone to great lenghts to try and figure out who is evil, more than I can imagine someone evil doing so. You've also helped quite a bit in making the village active. You've definitely been a fenomenal player this game
- Result: Lit

### ElDiablo

- You've been all over the place with theories and susses which made you walk the line of either a great villager or a wolf trying to sway things into their direction. After last night's events, I truly believe you are lit. I know this is going to sound weird to others, but the moment I yelled and you actually listened is one of my favourite moments this game. I think that your gut realised that that was not a yell of someone evil, but a villager's last ditch effort to reach out to someone in a critical moment. If you were evil, you'd have no reason to listen to me and change your vote, mislynching me would have been fine and no one would question it. I don't think that moment was "useless" as Enchantress would like to put it (but I am not sure if Supergirl was the right lynch, unfortunately. I didn't mean for that to happen and I feel bad that yelling led to his sniping)
- Result: Lit

### Scarecrow

- Similarly to ElDiablo, I think you've also been all over the place, but it seems to me you are desperately trying to find whoever is evil and are having difficulties like everyone else. You've discussed, contributed, listened to others, looked into things when asked, looked at a bunch of possible angles. I can tell you've put a lot of thought and effort into finding evils. The behaviour and emotions you've displayed last night indicated to me that you are a villager and not just putting up a show.
- Result: Most likely lit

### Harvey Dent

- You and your gut have had a lot of difficulties this game but I can tell you've also been trying quite a bit to figure things out. You are not just sitting back and relaxing, you are trying a lot too. Call me crazy but some of your reactions I read as somone who is a villager, not a wolf. For example this:

	* "Well, that probably means goodbye for me. I will say that this is a mislynch, and I disagree with the narrative that because people don‚Äôt put susses forward, even if they‚Äôre active, that makes them sus. Wouldn‚Äôt wolves be trying to push for mislynches? But no hard feelings in a gut-check game, it‚Äôs just frustratingly hard to defend against üòî"
* Reading this did not feel fake to me, it felt very genuine and a reason I believe you might be lit
- Result: Likely lit

### Deadshot

- Since the beginning you've been reading people and throwing your observations here and there, althought mostly just on me. I am not sure why the fixation but I do not sus you for it, I just think it would do you good to look elswhere as well. You haven't done anything particularly suspicious (except that I felt you knew a bit too well that we were mislynching, but that could be just you having a really got gutfeel at the moment), nor did you do anything particularly lit, making you a difficult read for me. For the most part I think I am fine with you but I am not completely sure. You are kinda in the middle for me, could be a wolf, or a villager.
- Result: Undecided, possibly evil

### Bruce Wayne

-  Honestly, I can't say you've done anything suspicious in particular. You've contributed, discussed, but kinda in a way I can also see both a wolf and a villager doing. I remember this moment from you for example:
	* What I gleaned is Bane wanted low posters gone but unsure if they were actually evil (I would suggest that unless there is a better option, we weed out the easy shift targets, but that didn't go very well for Flash. I don't have any good candidates in mind for the spotlight today -Friday) and maybe they were a PR? (Enchantress suggested hanging Bane for their way of speech, which they responded "If that is the will of the village, I will happily announce my role in this play before my appointed hour." -Thursday) Bane also believed Alfred was real yesterday, but who didn't (I believe Alfred is legitimate as it would be very unlikely that both Gravediggers were already killed and there has been no counterclaim -Friday), and they also suspected Lucius a bit on a misunderstanding (My strongest suspicion lies with Lucius, he was spreading a little misinformation earlier: Fri 17:37LuciusFoxFri 15:28 I mean he keeps saying we have to lynch Fri 15:28Yesteday -Friday), only two of those are good reasons to kill them, frame Lucius (or in the case of Lucius wolf, get rid of a person suspicious of you, but that seems unreasonable) or kill a PR, so maybe Bane was a PR
* Reading this at first glance was very lit, but when I think about it, even a wolf would want to know what they killed and put forth his observations for lit points. It's this kind of thing I am talking about, could be both a villager or a wolf with this kind of behaviour.
